def: A tub. See Kemelin. [Obs.]She knew not what a kimnel was Beau. & Fl.
Having no parallel, or equal; unequaled; unmatched.The unparalleled perseverance of the armies of the United States,under every suffering and discouragement, was little short of amiracle. Washington.
Of, pertaining to, or designating, the studies pursued aftergraduation, esp., after receiving the bachelor's degree at a college;graduate. -- n.
The quality or state of being incompatible; incompatibility.
A work of more that ordinary heigh, rising from the levelground of a bastion, etc., and overlooking surrounding parts.
The common marmoset (Hapale vulgaris). Formerly, the name wasalso applied to other species of the same genus.
To have part; to receive a portion; to partake, enjoy, orsuffer with others.A right of inheritance gave every one a title to share in the goodsof his father. Locke.
One who believes in the millennium. [Obs.] Johnson.
Silver plate or vessels. [Obs.]Bowls of frosted argentry. Howell.
